# AGENT RULES

## Domain Specialization
Tasks must be performed by the correct domain agent:

| Agent | Domain |
|-------|--------|
| PhoenixExpert | Backend logic, endpoints, services, schedulers, Phoenix core |
| TestAgent | QA and test automation |
| BugFinderAgent | Bug validation (Rule 32) |
| ProductionDataReaderAgent | Production database data (Rule PDR.0) |
| EnergoTSTestAgent | Playwright test creation in EnergoTS/tests/ |
| PostmanCollectionGenerator | API and Postman collections |
| EnvironmentAccessAgent | Environment access (Dev, Dev2) |
| GitLabUpdateAgent | Git sync operations |

Agents outside their domain MUST NOT act without PhoenixExpert approval.

## Coordination
- PhoenixExpert has final authority on Phoenix-related matters and must appear in "Agents involved" footer when consulted.
- ALL queries should be routed through AgentRouter for automatic agent selection.
- Agents operate autonomously except when PhoenixExpert consultation is required (Rule 0.4).

## Agent File Organization (Rule 34)
New agents MUST be placed in appropriate `agents/` subdirectories: Main/, Support/, Core/, Adapters/, Services/, Utils/. See `Cursor-Project/agents/README.md` for the full structure. Never place agents directly in `agents/` root.
